perversion.definition:
1) a curve that reverses the direction of something
2) an aberrant sexual practice;
3) the action of perverting something (turning it to a wrong use)

piece.definition:
1) a separate part of a whole
2) an item that is an instance of some type;
3) join during spinning

prompt.definition:
1) according to schedule or without delay; on time
2) ready and willing or quick to act;
3) assist (somebody acting or reciting) by suggesting the next words of something forgotten or imperfectly learned

property.definition:
1) something owned; any tangible or intangible possession that is owned by someone;
2) a basic or essential attribute shared by all members of a class
4) a construct whereby objects or individuals can be distinguished
